    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vault Integration in CI/CD Pipelines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GitHub Actions secrets and AWS SSM are convenient for small teams, but they lack the fine-grained access control, dynamic secret generation, and comprehensive audit logging that production secrets management requires. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HashiCorp Vault",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " fills this gap: it acts as a central secrets broker that authenticates callers by identity (OIDC JWT, Kubernetes service account), issues short-lived leases, and logs every secret read to an immutable audit trail."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The difference between storing a secret in GitHub Actions and fetching it from Vault is the difference between trusting a file and trusting an identity. Vault issues secrets only to authenticated, authorised callers \u2014 and logs every issuance."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This sub-subtopic covers Vault's JWT auth method for GitHub Actions, Kubernetes auth for application pods, the KV v2 secret engine pattern for Claude API keys, and the audit log configuration that makes all access traceable."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Vault CI/CD integration: GitHub Actions OIDC auth, Kubernetes sidecar injection, secret backends, and audit log",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JWT Auth Method for GitHub Actions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GitHub Actions generates an OIDC JWT for each workflow run. Vault's JWT auth method validates this token against GitHub's JWKS endpoint and issues a Vault token scoped to a specific policy. The runner never holds a long-lived Vault credential \u2014 the JWT proves identity, and the resulting Vault token expires when the job ends."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Vault configuration (run once by an admin)\n# Enable JWT auth and point it at GitHub's OIDC issuer\nvault auth enable jwt\n\nvault write auth/jwt/config \\\n  oidc_discovery_url=\"https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com\" \\\n  bound_issuer=\"https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com\"\n\n# Create a policy: read-only access to the claude key path\nvault policy write claude-ci - <<'EOF'\npath \"secret/data/ci/claude/*\" {\n  capabilities = [\"read\"]\n}\nEOF\n\n# Create a role: only jobs in this repo's main branch can assume it\nvault write auth/jwt/role/claude-ci-role \\\n  role_type=\"jwt\" \\\n  bound_audiences=\"https://vault.example.com\" \\\n  user_claim=\"sub\" \\\n  bound_claims='{\"repository\":\"org/repo\",\"ref\":\"refs/heads/main\"}' \\\n  policies=\"claude-ci\" \\\n  ttl=\"15m\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/deploy.yml \u2014 fetch secrets from Vault\nname: Deploy\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # required for OIDC token generation\n  contents: read\n\njobs:\n  deploy:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Import secrets from Vault\n        uses: hashicorp/vault-action@v3\n        with:\n          url: ${{ vars.VAULT_ADDR }}\n          method: jwt\n          role: claude-ci-role\n          secrets: |\n            secret/data/ci/claude/api_key value | ANTHROPIC_API_KEY ;\n            secret/data/ci/claude/webhook_secret value | WEBHOOK_SECRET\n\n      - name: Run eval suite\n        env:\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n        run: python3 scripts/run_evals.py\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "vault-action",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " step exchanges the OIDC JWT for a Vault token, reads each secret path, and injects the values as masked environment variables. The Vault token is valid for 15 minutes \u2014 long enough for the job, short enough that it cannot be used after the workflow ends."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Storing the Claude API Key in Vault KV v2"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "KV v2 is Vault's versioned key-value secret engine. It maintains a version history for every secret, allowing point-in-time recovery and audit of what value was active at any point:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Enable KV v2 at the path 'secret/'\nvault secrets enable -path=secret kv-v2\n\n# Write the Claude API key for the CI workload\nvault kv put secret/ci/claude/api_key \\\n  value=\"sk-ant-api03-...\"\n\n# Write the production key at a separate path (different policy)\nvault kv put secret/prod/claude/api_key \\\n  value=\"sk-ant-api03-...\"\n\n# Verify\nvault kv get secret/ci/claude/api_key\n# Key                Value\n# ---                -----\n# created_time       2025-07-01T08:00:00Z\n# current_version    1\n# value              sk-ant-api03-...\n\n# After rotation \u2014 write new version\nvault kv put secret/ci/claude/api_key value=\"sk-ant-api03-NEW...\"\nvault kv get secret/ci/claude/api_key  # current_version = 2\n\n# Roll back if needed\nvault kv rollback -version=1 secret/ci/claude/api_key\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "KV v2 metadata lets you attach rotation policy hints as custom metadata:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "vault kv metadata put \\\n  -custom-metadata rotate_after=\"2025-08-01\" \\\n  -custom-metadata owner=\"@alice\" \\\n  -custom-metadata workload=\"ci\" \\\n  secret/ci/claude/api_key\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Kubernetes Auth for Application Pods"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Application pods authenticate to Vault using their Kubernetes service account JWT \u2014 no static credentials required. The Vault Agent sidecar handles token renewal and secret injection transparently:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Enable Kubernetes auth method\nvault auth enable kubernetes\n\nvault write auth/kubernetes/config \\\n  kubernetes_host=\"https://kubernetes.default.svc\" \\\n  kubernetes_ca_cert=@/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/ca.crt \\\n  token_reviewer_jwt=@/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n\n# Policy: prod app can read only prod secrets\nvault policy write claude-prod - <<'EOF'\npath \"secret/data/prod/claude/*\" {\n  capabilities = [\"read\"]\n}\nEOF\n\n# Role: only pods using the 'claude-api' service account in 'prod' namespace\nvault write auth/kubernetes/role/claude-prod-role \\\n  bound_service_account_names=\"claude-api\" \\\n  bound_service_account_namespaces=\"prod\" \\\n  policies=\"claude-prod\" \\\n  ttl=\"1h\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# k8s/deployment.yaml \u2014 Vault Agent sidecar injection\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: claude-api\n  namespace: prod\nspec:\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      annotations:\n        vault.hashicorp.com/agent-inject: \"true\"\n        vault.hashicorp.com/role: \"claude-prod-role\"\n        vault.hashicorp.com/agent-inject-secret-api-key: \"secret/data/prod/claude/api_key\"\n        vault.hashicorp.com/agent-inject-template-api-key: |\n          {{- with secret \"secret/data/prod/claude/api_key\" -}}\n          export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"{{ .Data.data.value }}\"\n          {{- end }}\n    spec:\n      serviceAccountName: claude-api\n      containers:\n        - name: app\n          image: claude-api:latest\n          command: [\"/bin/sh\", \"-c\"]\n          args:\n            - source /vault/secrets/api-key && exec python3 -m uvicorn app.main:app\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Vault Agent sidecar renews the lease automatically. When the Claude API key is rotated in Vault, the Agent picks up the new version on the next lease renewal without a pod restart \u2014 lease TTL drives the maximum staleness."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Audit Log Configuration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every Vault secret read generates an audit log entry containing the caller's identity, the secret path, the timestamp, and the client token. Enable a file audit backend and ship the log to your SIEM:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Enable audit logging to a file (also supports syslog, socket)\nvault audit enable file file_path=/vault/logs/audit.log\n\n# Verify audit is enabled\nvault audit list\n# Path     Type    Description\n# ----     ----    -----------\n# file/    file    n/a\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A single audit log entry (HMAC-redacted, from Vault docs format):"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\n  \"time\": \"2025-07-01T09:15:32.123Z\",\n  \"type\": \"response\",\n  \"auth\": {\n    \"client_token\": \"hmac-sha256:abc123...\",\n    \"accessor\": \"hmac-sha256:def456...\",\n    \"display_name\": \"jwt-github-actions-org/repo\",\n    \"policies\": [\"claude-ci\"],\n    \"token_issue_time\": \"2025-07-01T09:15:00Z\"\n  },\n  \"request\": {\n    \"id\": \"uuid-...\",\n    \"operation\": \"read\",\n    \"path\": \"secret/data/ci/claude/api_key\",\n    \"remote_address\": \"10.0.0.15\"\n  },\n  \"response\": {\n    \"data\": {\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"created_time\": \"2025-07-01T08:00:00Z\",\n        \"version\": 2\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The secret value is never logged \u2014 only metadata. All token values are HMAC-hashed in the log, so the audit file is safe to ship to a log aggregation service without redaction."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
