      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dynamic Secrets for Database Credentials"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beyond static key-value secrets, Vault's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "database secrets engine",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " generates short-lived database credentials on demand \u2014 each CI job gets its own unique username/password pair that expires when the job ends. This eliminates shared credentials entirely for databases used in integration tests:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Enable the database secrets engine\nvault secrets enable database\n\n# Configure a PostgreSQL connection\nvault write database/config/claude-test-db \\\n  plugin_name=\"postgresql-database-plugin\" \\\n  connection_url=\"postgresql://{{username}}:{{password}}@db.example.com:5432/testdb\" \\\n  allowed_roles=\"ci-test-role\" \\\n  username=\"vault-admin\" \\\n  password=\"initial-admin-password\"\n\n# Create a role: each lease gets a unique user valid for 1 hour\nvault write database/roles/ci-test-role \\\n  db_name=\"claude-test-db\" \\\n  creation_statements=\"CREATE ROLE \\\"{{name}}\\\" WITH LOGIN PASSWORD '{{password}}' VALID UNTIL '{{expiration}}'; GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO \\\"{{name}}\\\";\" \\\n  default_ttl=\"1h\" \\\n  max_ttl=\"2h\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/integration-test.yml\n# Each job run gets its own ephemeral DB credentials\nname: Integration Tests\n\non: [pull_request]\n\npermissions:\n  id-token: write\n  contents: read\n\njobs:\n  test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Fetch dynamic DB credentials from Vault\n        uses: hashicorp/vault-action@v3\n        with:\n          url: ${{ vars.VAULT_ADDR }}\n          method: jwt\n          role: claude-ci-role\n          secrets: |\n            database/creds/ci-test-role username | DB_USER ;\n            database/creds/ci-test-role password | DB_PASSWORD ;\n            secret/data/ci/claude/api_key value  | ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n\n      - name: Run integration tests\n        env:\n          DATABASE_URL: postgresql://${{ env.DB_USER }}:${{ env.DB_PASSWORD }}@db.example.com/testdb\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n        run: pytest tests/integration/ -v\n\n      # When the job ends, Vault automatically revokes DB_USER and DB_PASSWORD\n      # The user no longer exists in Postgres after TTL expiry\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dynamic credentials solve the rotation problem at source: because each lease is unique and short-lived, there is nothing to rotate \u2014 compromising a credential is harmless after the TTL expires."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vault in the Local Development Workflow"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Engineers running the application locally need the same secrets without bypassing Vault. The Vault CLI can authenticate via browser-based OIDC and cache a short-lived token:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Developer one-time setup: authenticate to Vault via browser\nvault login -method=oidc\n\n# Read the dev Claude API key into a local env file (never committed)\nvault kv get -field=value secret/dev/claude/api_key > .env.local\necho \"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=$(vault kv get -field=value secret/dev/claude/api_key)\" > .env.local\n\n# Or use envconsul to keep env vars refreshed while developing\nenvconsul \\\n  -vault-addr=\"$VAULT_ADDR\" \\\n  -secret=\"secret/data/dev/claude/api_key\" \\\n  python3 -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .gitignore \u2014 never commit local secrets\n.env.local\n.vault-token\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Vault token cached locally by `vault login` defaults to a 32-hour TTL \u2014 enough for a full working day. Engineers re-authenticate the next morning. This is safer than long-lived API keys in `.env` files that migrate from machine to machine unnoticed."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
